# Error Handling Standards

## Error Handling Policy
- **DO NOT throw exceptions** - return empty/default values instead (e.g., return empty vector, nullptr, or default-constructed object).
- Use RAII for resource management to avoid memory leaks.
- Validate inputs at function boundaries.

## Logging
- Log errors using the provided logging library wrapper, which can be found at 'Engine/src/logger/log.h'.
- The logging library wraps spdlog. 
- Use the correct category and type depending on the location and purpose of the logs.
- **DO NOT include function names in log messages** - the logging macro will handle this automatically.
